# Histogram for visibility
from matplotlib.ticker import MultipleLocator  # import this

# Define bin edges (bin width 20)
min_vis = df['visibility(mi)'].min()
max_vis = df['visibility(mi)'].max()
bins = np.arange(min_vis, max_vis + 10, 10)

# Compute histogram
counts, bin_edges = np.histogram(df['visibility(mi)'], bins=bins)
percentages = counts / counts.sum() * 100

# Normalize counts to full height (100%)
normalized_heights = np.ones_like(counts) * 100  # full height bars

# Plot histogram with all bars full height
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
bars = plt.bar(
    (bin_edges[:-1] + bin_edges[1:]) / 2,  # bin centers
    normalized_heights,
    width=(bin_edges[1] - bin_edges[0]) * 0.9,
    color="skyblue",
    edgecolor="black"
)

# Add percentage text inside each bar (rotated 90)
for bar, pct in zip(bars, percentages):
    if pct > 0:
        plt.text(
            bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2,
            50,                # middle of full-height bar
            f"{pct:.3f}%",
            ha="center",
            va="center",
            rotation=90,
            fontsize=10,
            fontweight="bold",
            color="black"
        )

# Titles & labels
plt.title("Distribution of Visibility", fontsize=14, fontweight="bold")
plt.xlabel("Visibility (Mi)", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("Percentage of Accidents (%)", fontsize=12)

# X-axis ticks every 10
plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(MultipleLocator(10))

# Y-axis 0-100%
plt.ylim(0, 100)

plt.show()

Observations: Based on meteorological knowledge and typical observed values in the U.S., following plausible ranges for selected variables in the U.S. road accident data analysis can be defined:

  • Temperatur (F): 60 - 130 (Covers extreme Alaska lows to Death Valley high)
  • Wind Chill (F): -80 - 130
  • Visibility (mi): 0 - 40 (0: No visibility (dense fog, blizzard), 10: Clear, > 40: Not meaningful (sky is clear)).
  • Wind Speed (mph): 0 - 120 (0: Calm, 60 - 100: Strong (Huricanes, Tornados, >120: Unlikely Outliers)
  • Precipitation (in): 0 - 6 (2 - 3: Heavy rainfall, 6: Unrealistic) --> inches/hour)

- Cleaning Outliers

In[26]:
# Define plausible ranges
plausible_ranges = {
    'temperature(f)': (-60, 130),
    'wind_chill(f)': (-80, 130),
    'visibility(mi)': (0, 40),
    'wind_speed(mph)': (0, 120),
    'precipitation(in)': (0, 6)
}

# Make a copy of the dataframe to keep the original dataframe
df_drop = df.copy()

# Drop rows with outliers based on plausible ranges
for col, (low, high) in plausible_ranges.items():
    df_drop = df_drop[df_drop[col].between(low, high)]

print("Original dataframe shape:", df.shape)
print("Cleaned dataframe shape:", df_drop.shape)

Original dataframe shape: (7481728, 29)
Cleaned dataframe shape: (7477440, 29)

# Shapes
original_shape = (7481728, 29)
cleaned_shape = (7477440, 29)

# Extract row counts
original_rows = original_shape[0]

# Aggregate number of accidents per state
data_to_plot = df_drop['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
data_to_plot.columns = ['state', 'count']  # 'count' = number of accidents

# Take log of counts for color scaling (handles large differences)
data_to_plot['log_count'] = np.log1p(data_to_plot['count'])  # log(1 + count)

# Reindex for attaching properties
state_data_indexed = data_to_plot.set_index('state')

# Setup Folium map centered on US
choropleth = folium.Map(location=[37.8, -96], zoom_start=4)

# Create choropleth with log_count
cp = folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=usa_geo,                   # GeoJSON for US states
    data=data_to_plot,
    columns=['state', 'log_count'],     # use log_count for coloring
    key_on='feature.properties.name',
    fill_color='YlOrRd',                # yellow-orange-red color scale
    fill_opacity=0.7,
    line_opacity=0.2,
    legend_name='Number of Accidents',  # indicate log scale
    nan_fill_color="white"
).add_to(choropleth)

# Attach actual accident counts to each state for tooltip
for s in cp.geojson.data['features']:
    state_name = s['properties']['name']
    if state_name in state_data_indexed.index:
        s['properties']['count'] = int(state_data_indexed.loc[state_name, 'count'])
    else:
        s['properties']['count'] = 0

# Add tooltip (shows actual count on hover)
folium.GeoJsonTooltip(
    fields=['name', 'count'],
    aliases=['State:', 'Accidents:'],
    localize=True
).add_to(cp.geojson)

# Add layer control
folium.LayerControl().add_to(choropleth)

4.2: Severity distribution across states

  • Hypothesis: Severe accidents (Serious/Major) occur more frequently in some states than others.
In[31]:
# Filter only severe accidents (Serious/Major)
severe_accidents = df_drop[df_drop['severity_label'].isin(['Serious', 'Major'])]

# Count severe accidents per state
severe_counts = severe_accidents['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
severe_counts.columns = ['state', 'severe_count']

# Count total accidents per state (for normalization)
total_counts = df_drop['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
total_counts.columns = ['state', 'total_count']

# Merge severe and total counts
state_severity = pd.merge(severe_counts, total_counts, on='state', how='right')
state_severity['severe_count'] = state_severity['severe_count'].fillna(0)

# Calculate proportion of severe accidents
state_severity['severe_ratio'] = state_severity['severe_count'] / state_severity['total_count']

# Reindex for attaching properties later
state_data_indexed = state_severity.set_index('state')

# Setup Folium map
choropleth = folium.Map(location=[37.8, -96], zoom_start=4)

# Create choropleth based on severe_ratio
cp = folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=usa_geo,
    data=state_severity,
    columns=['state', 'severe_ratio'],
    key_on='feature.properties.name',   # must match GeoJSON 'name'
    fill_color='YlOrRd',
    fill_opacity=0.7,
    line_opacity=0.2,
    legend_name='Proportion of Severe Accidents'
).add_to(choropleth)

# Attach severe_ratio + counts to each state polygon for tooltip
for s in cp.geojson.data['features']:
    state_name = s['properties']['name']
    if state_name in state_data_indexed.index:
        s['properties']['severe_ratio']  = round(state_data_indexed.loc[state_name, 'severe_ratio'], 3)
        s['properties']['severe_count']  = int(state_data_indexed.loc[state_name, 'severe_count'])
        s['properties']['total_count']   = int(state_data_indexed.loc[state_name, 'total_count'])
    else:
        s['properties']['severe_ratio']  = 0
        s['properties']['severe_count']  = 0
        s['properties']['total_count']   = 0

# Add tooltip (hover popup)
folium.GeoJsonTooltip(
    fields=['name', 'severe_count', 'total_count', 'severe_ratio'],
    aliases=['State:', 'Severe accidents:', 'Total accidents:', 'Severe ratio:'],
    localize=True
).add_to(cp.geojson)

# Layer control
folium.LayerControl().add_to(choropleth)
